FBIS3-31885 "dreeu039aa_94004" FBIS-EEU-94-039 Document Type:Daily Report 28 February 1994 INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS Belgian Troops in Croatia Sent to Bosnia LD2602192194 Brussels La Une Radio Network in French 1700 GMT 26 Feb 94 LD2602192194 Brussels La Une Radio Network Language: French Article Type:BFN [Excerpts] In Bosnia the cease-fire between Croats and Muslims has been respected on the whole, UN forces have said. [passage omitted] Belgium will be sending UN soldiers. Soon 150 Belgian UN soldiers will leave Baranja, in eastern Croatia, for central Bosnia. A vanguard of a dozen Belgian soldiers has already left. The Belgian infantry is equipped with some 15 armored vehicles. The number of Belgian troops in Bosnia will thus total some 450 soldiers.
